On Jue 23rd the firm invoiced 110 sheets (13,200) of One Penny and 58 sheets (6,960) of Sixpence at 3/4d per 1,000, showing theat the Crown Agents supplied the apper. they did not make any charge for overprint plate. the sheets were in multiples of 120.

Two further supplies of Sixpence were sent on November 6, 1877 (52 sheets) and April 30, 1881 (51 sheets). the overprintted On Penny was printed eleven times, and remained in current use until the separate issues for Montserrat were suspended in 1890.
